0.title: Rules
0.body:
To place a building in a district, drag it from its stack and drop it in the appropriate location.  Snap points ensure that the building will be aligned neatly.

To add a service marker to a district, click on the square underneath the service icon.  A block of your color will be added, and the King's Bonus chart will be updated automatically.  Click on the square again to remove the block.  Players can only add or remove their own blocks.

When your score pass 100, left-click on the "+100" button and the number "100" will appear on your marker.  Click again and it will change to 200.  A third-click removes the number.  Right-clicking on the button will add the number to the City Marker.

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    local params = {
        click_function = "clickLevyFunds",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "Collect",
        position       = {-2, 0.2, 0.75},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 400,
        height         = 150,
        font_size      = 100,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Click to collect money"
    }

    -- Create the button for Levy Funds
    self.createButton(params)

    -- Create the button for Tax and Build
    params.click_function = "clickTaxBuild"
    params.position = {2, 0.2, 0.75}
    self.createButton(params)
end

-- Returns a random number between -1 and 1
function random()
    return (math.random() * 2) - 1
end

function collectMoney(money)
    local targetZone = getObjectFromGUID("67f67f")
    local zoneSize = targetZone.getScale()

    local denominations = {10, 5, 1}
    local moneyBags = {
        [1] = getObjectFromGUID("871136"),
        [5] = getObjectFromGUID("3fbf02"),
        [10] = getObjectFromGUID("2a92a3"),
    }

    local params = {
        smooth = false,
    }
    local height = 3

    for _,v in pairs(denominations) do
        while money >= v do
            local pos = targetZone.getPosition()
            pos.x = pos.x + random() * zoneSize.x / 4
            pos.z = pos.z + random() * zoneSize.z / 4
            pos.y = pos.y + height
            params.position = pos
            moneyBags[v].takeObject(params)

            height = height + 1
            money = money - v
        end
    end
end

function getMoney()
    local gameBoard = getObjectFromGUID("e2f237")
    local cityMarker = getObjectFromGUID("6bff57")
    local score = gameBoard.call("markerScore", cityMarker)

    return math.floor((score - 1) / 10) + 5
end

function clickLevyFunds(obj, color, alt_click)
    local money = getMoney()
    collectMoney(money)
end

function clickTaxBuild(obj, color, alt_click)
    local money = getMoney()
    collectMoney(math.floor(money / 2))
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Tile
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
owner = nil -- who owns this tile
stack_zone = nil -- the scripting zone that covers the tile stack
colormap = {Red = {0.75, 0, 0}, Green = {0.25, 0.63, 0.2}, Blue = {0.1, 0.35, 0.65}, Yellow = {1, 1, 0}}

function onLoad(save_state)
    if save_state ~= "" then
        owner = save_state
    end

    stack_zone = getObjectFromGUID('84c367')
end

-- if a player picks up a piece and it's not already owned, then assign it
function onPickUp(player)
    color = colormap[player]

    if not color then
        print("Unknown color ", player)
        return
    end

    if owner == nil then
        owner = player
        self.setColorTint(color)
    end
end

-- if the player drops the piece back on its stack, then reset it
function onDrop(player)
    local inStack = false

    for _,v in ipairs(stack_zone.getObjects()) do
        if v == self then
            owner = nil
            self.setColorTint({0.7, 0.7, 0.7}) -- grey
            break
        end
    end
end

function onSave()
    return owner or ""
end

ObjectStates.Name: BlockSquare
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    local params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "+100",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 500,
        font_size      = 300,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Left-click to increment your score marker, right-click to increment the city score marker. This button replaces the 100/200 score tokens and the city discs."
    }

    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    local marker

    if alt_click then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('6bff57')
    elseif color == "Green" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('a0ccfc')
    elseif color == "Yellow" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('c4ec6a')
    elseif color == "Red" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('237668')
    elseif color == "Blue" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('5d159c')
    else
        print("Unknown color ", color)
        return
    end

    marker.call("increment")
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad(save_state)
    local left = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        position       = {0.38, 0.94, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 270, 37},
        label          = save_state,
        width          = 0,
        height         = 0,
        font_size      = 270,
        color          = {0.1, 0.35, 0.65},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    local right = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        position       = {-0.38, 0.94, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 90, -37},
        label          = save_state,
        width          = 0,
        height         = 0,
        font_size      = 270,
        color          = {0.1, 0.35, 0.65},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }

    self.createButton(left)
    self.createButton(right)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
end

table = {
    [""] = "100",
    ["100"] = "200",
    ["200"] = "300",
    ["300"] = "",
}

function increment()
    -- Assume that both sides have the same value
    local button = self.getButtons()[1]
    local label = table[button.label]

    self.editButton({index = 0, label=label})
    self.editButton({index = 1, label=label})
end

function onSave()
    local button = self.getButtons()[1]

    return button.label
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Tile
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
-- The collection of all the buttons, without or without cubes
buttons_set = {}

function onLoad(save_state_json)
    local co = -0.844 -- column offset
    local cs = 0.3565 -- column scale
    local bs = 0.0526 -- button offset
    local ro = -0.576 -- row offset
    local rs = 0.3565 -- row scale
    local save_state = nil

    if save_state_json ~= "" then
        -- The save state contains the list of all 149 buttons, but the
        -- JSON has to be decoded.  But first, let's verify it.
        save_state = JSON.decode(save_state_json)

        if #save_state ~= 149 then
            broadcastToAll("Saved state is corrupted!", Color.Red)
            save_state = nil
        end
    end

    if save_state ~= nil then
        for _,button in ipairs(save_state) do
            c = button.column
            r = button.row
            b = button.service
            local button_data = {
                position = {x = co + (c * cs) + (b * bs), y = 0.1, z = ro + (r * rs)},
                cube = getObjectFromGUID(button.cube_guid),
                token = getObjectFromGUID(button.token_guid),
                cube_color = button.cube_color,
                column = c,
                row = r,
                service = b,
            }
            table.insert(buttons_set, button_data)
        end
    else
        for c = 0,4 do
            for r = 0,4 do
                for b = 0,5 do
                    -- skip the city service marker
                    if not (c == 2 and r == 2 and b == 0) then
                        local button_data = {
                            position = {x = co + (c * cs) + (b * bs), y = 0.1, z = ro + (r * rs)},
                            cube = nil, -- the cube object that's placed on this token
                            token = nil, -- the score token object moved by the button on this cube
                            cube_color = nil, -- the color of the cube on this button
                            column = c,
                            row = r,
                            service = b,
                        }
                        table.insert(buttons_set, button_data)
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end

    for _,button0 in ipairs(buttons_set) do
        local button = {
            width = 20,
            height = 20,
            color = {0, 0, 0, 0},
            hover_color = {0, 0, 0, 0.7},
            press_color = {0, 0, 0, 0},
            function_owner = self,
            click_function = "button"..button0.column..button0.row..button0.service,
            position = button0.position,
        }

        local func = function(obj, player, alt_click)
            buttonClicked(obj, player, alt_click, button0)
        end
        self.setVar("button"..button0.column..button0.row..button0.service, func)
        self.createButton(button)
    end
end

scoreToken = {
--          green     red       yellow    blue     neutral
    [0] = {'0de0a6', '3322fd', '289467', '98c6fd', '1dee61'}, -- water
    [1] = {'ed27ad', '5eb69a', '3d5d30', '71aaaf', '60fb49'}, -- food
    [2] = {'5808d7', '554ff6', 'e6b3dc', 'f14de0', '4b3bc4'}, -- religion
    [3] = {'a524d6', '881675', 'c8c173', '946adc', 'b81b1e'}, -- defense
    [4] = {'40acb1', '8a73ef', '212edc', 'b6ccbc', 'ba1fd4'}, -- commerce
    [5] = {'7f1cbf', '204a31', '55a0b9', 'abe989', '070f23'}, -- culture
}

function buttonClicked(board, player, alt_click, button)
    local token
    local cubeBag
    local score
    local index = button.service

    if button.cube then
        -- Right-button click in a two-player game is used to place neutral cubes
        if alt_click then
            if button.cube_color ~= "Neutral" then
                return
            end
        else
            -- only allow a player to remove his own cubes
            if button.cube_color ~= player then
                return
            end
        end
        token = button.token
        score = token.getVar("score") - 1

        destroyObject(button.cube)
        button.cube = nil
        button.token = nil
        button.cube_color = nil
    else
        if alt_click then
            if #getSeatedPlayers() == 2 then
                cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("e25a01")
                token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][5])
            else
                -- Only add a neutral token if we're in a two-player game
                return
            end
        elseif player == "Red" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("551726")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][2])
        elseif player == "Green" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("c9ae8b")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][1])
        elseif player == "Blue" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("97bcca")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][4])
        elseif player == "Yellow" then
            cubeBag = getObjectFromGUID("fd6678")
            token = getObjectFromGUID(scoreToken[index][3])
        else
            print('Unrecognize color ', player)
            return
        end

        score = token.getVar("score") + 1

        -- We have to invert the X-axis for some log(button)
        local buttonPos = {-button.position.x, button.position.y, button.position.z}
        local params = {
            smooth = false,
            position = board.positionToWorld(buttonPos),
        }
        button.cube = cubeBag.takeObject(params) -- take the cube from the cube Bag
        button.token = token
        if alt_click then
            button.cube_color = "Neutral"
        else
            button.cube_color = player
        end
    end

    token.setVar("score", score)
    if score > 14 then
        -- Maximum score displayed is 14, but we want to be able to track
        -- scores higher than that, just in case.
        score = 14
    end

    local tokenPos = token.getPosition()
    tokenPos.x = -0.9011 + 1.4 * score
    tokenPos.y = 2
    token.setPosition(tokenPos)
end

function markerScore(marker)
    local pos = self.positionToLocal(marker.getPosition())
    local score = 0

    -- These give either -1 or a number between 1 and 25
    local x = math.floor(((pos.x * -100) + 93.6) / 7.5 + 0.1)
    local z = math.floor(((pos.z * -100) + 94.6) / 7.5 + 0.1)

    -- first, make some corrections for the corners, which are not aligned
    if x < 0 then
        x = 0
    end
    if z < 1 then
        z = 0
    end

    -- calculate the score between 0 and 99
    if z == 25 then
        score = x
    elseif x == 25 then
        score = 50 - z
    elseif z == 0 then
        score = 75 - x
    else
        score = 75 + z
    end

    -- Add the +100 bonus score if present
    local button = marker.getButtons()[1]
    if button.label ~= "" then
        score = score + tonumber(button.label)
    end

    return score
end

function onSave()
    -- Save the entire button array.  It would be take a lot less space if
    -- we just saved the buttons that have cubes on them, but then it would
    -- be a lot more work to parse that.
    save_state = {}
    for _,button in ipairs(buttons_set) do
        local state = {
            -- objects can't be encoded, so convert them to GUIDs
            cube_guid = button.cube and button.cube.getGUID() or nil,
            token_guid = button.token and button.token.getGUID() or nil,
            cube_color = button.cube_color,
            column = button.column,
            row = button.row,
            service = button.service,
        }
        table.insert(save_state, state)
    end

    return JSON.encode(save_state)
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
orderTokenGUIDs = {
    "7ed858", -- Saxon Prince
    "e67c99", -- Saxon Duke
    "39477f", -- Saxon Count
    "886874", -- Saxon Earl
}
orderBag = nil

function onLoad()
    local params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "Start\nGame",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 1000,
        font_size      = 300,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Click here once all players are seated."
    }

    self.createButton(params)
    orderBag = getObjectFromGUID("9566ac")
end

-- returns the index of table where 'value' exist, or 0
function findIndex(table, value)
    for k,v in pairs(table) do
        if v == value then
            return k
        end
    end

    return 0
end

-- Returns the top two tiles
function topTiles(zone)
    local tiles = {nil, nil}

    -- the heights of the two highest tiles so far
    local heights = {0, 0}

    for k,v in pairs(zone.getObjects()) do
        local pos = v.getPosition()

        -- if the new height is higher than the current top, then it becomes
        -- the new top, and the previous top because second place
        if pos.y > heights[1] then
            tiles[2] = tiles[1]
            tiles[1] = v
            heights[1] = pos.y
        -- otherwise, if the new height is in between the top two heights,
        -- then it becomes the new second place
        elseif pos.y > heights[2] then
            tiles[2] = v
            heights[2] = pos.y
        end
    end

    return tiles
end

-- Create the remaining clones of all the structure tiles
-- We do this so that we don't need to create the clones manually.
-- That makes it easier to maintain the code for the tiles.
function createStructureTileClones()
    -- But first, we only want to do this if there are no clones at all.
    -- That is a pristine board.
    for _,v in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        if v.getGMNotes() == "clone" then
            -- If there's at least one clone on the board,
            -- then assume that they all exist.
            print("Continuing game in progress")
            return
        end
    end

    local tiles = {
        { "55f02e", 11 }, -- small structures
        { "1d9538", 11 },
        { "fbf9c8", 8 },
        { "0db045", 8 },
        { "6e8c71", 5 },
        { "564ba1", 5 },
        { "c05fff", 5 }, -- medium structures
        { "378eb3", 5 },
        { "4d6a48", 4 },
        { "fddac6", 4 },
        { "54137a", 3 },
        { "1c7cef", 3},
    }

    for _,v in ipairs(tiles) do
        local tile = getObjectFromGUID(v[1])
        local pos = tile.getPosition()

        for i = 1,v[2] do
            pos.y = 1 + i / 4.0
            local params = {
                position = pos,
                snap_to_grid = true,
            }

            local clone = tile.clone(params)
            clone.setGMNotes("clone")
        end
    end
end

function twoPlayers(seatedOrder)
    -- The scripting zones of each small and medium tile stack
    local sourceZoneGUIDs = {
        -- Small, from right to left
        { "80c9b0", "2bf2e1", "6f5c54", "3725cd", "9c1045", "4a6642"},
        -- Medium, from right to left
        { "c1a842", "5ad5ea", "057f91", "77bdf6", "c26c72", "4819cb"},
    }

    -- each player has a pair of zones next to his board that old the
    -- stacks of structures for the neutral player.
    local targetZoneGUIDs = {
        --         small     medium    build token
        Red =    { "c7a89a", "68f179", "fd003f" },
        Green =  { "8c0c34", "bd48f8", "71cf7f" },
        Blue =   { "d4314d", "eb8643", "bb551a" },
        Yellow = { "a6e79d", "fab66a", "7fd04a" },
    }

    -- The actual build/nobuild tokens, one for each player
    local buildTokensGUIDs = { "24da88", "e42c68" }

    -- Distribute all 24 tiles to four stacks, and give each player a
    -- build / no-build token

    -- first build the small structure stacks, then the medium structure stacks
    -- index==1 -> small structures, index==2 -> medium structures
    for sizeIndex = 1,2 do
        -- iterate over each of the stacks
        for tileIndex,sourceZoneGuid in pairs(sourceZoneGUIDs[sizeIndex]) do
            local sourceZone = getObjectFromGUID(sourceZoneGuid)
            local tiles = topTiles(sourceZone)

            -- tiles[1] is the top tile of the stack, tiles[2] is under it
            for playerNumber,tile in pairs(tiles) do
                local playerColor = seatedOrder[playerNumber]

                -- target zone for this stack
                local targetZoneGUID = targetZoneGUIDs[playerColor][sizeIndex]
                local targetZone = getObjectFromGUID(targetZoneGUID)

                -- setPosition() returns quickly, before it's finished moving
                -- the tile.  If we try to move all of the tiles of one stack
                -- to the same position, they will crash into each other.
                -- So instead, we layer the tiles in mid-air.  They will then fall
                -- down in a neat stack together.
                local pos = targetZone.getPosition()
                pos.y = pos.y + tileIndex / 2.0
                tile.setPosition(pos)

                -- Also mark the tile as being owned by the Neutral player
                tile.setVar("owner", "Neutral")
                tile.setColorTint({0.5, 0.5, 0.5})
            end
        end
    end

    -- And now the build / no-build tokens, which are kept in the same
    -- bag as the order tiles
    for playerNumber = 1,2 do
        local playerColor = seatedOrder[playerNumber]
        local targetZoneGUID = targetZoneGUIDs[playerColor][3]
        local targetZone = getObjectFromGUID(targetZoneGUID)
        local params = {
            smooth = false,
            position = targetZone.getPosition(),
            guid = buildTokensGUIDs[playerNumber],
        }
        orderBag.takeObject(params) -- grab the token
    end
end

-- Remove tokens for colors that are not playing.  It's easier in TTS to
-- remove unwanted objects than it is to create them via code
function deleteOtherPlayers(players)
    -- List of objects to remove for each color
    local playerTokens = {
        -- Score token, king's bonus tokens, player mat, player pawn
        Red = { "237668", "204a31", "3322fd", "554ff6", "5eb69a", "881675", "8a73ef", "aa2037", "bd0da8" },
        Green = { "a0ccfc", "0de0a6", "40acb1", "5808d7", "7f1cbf", "a524d6", "ed27ad", "3c489f", "e88e72"},
        Blue = { "5d159c", "71aaaf", "946adc", "98c6fd", "abe989", "b6ccbc", "f14de0", "fe9bbb", "55d8d6" },
        Yellow = { "c4ec6a", "212edc", "289467", "3d5d30", "55a0b9", "c8c173", "e6b3dc", "4f60c5", "320610" },
        -- king's bonus tokens only
        Neutral = { "1dee61", "4b3bc4", "60fb49", "070f23", "b81b1e", "ba1fd4" }
    }

    for _,playerColor in ipairs(players) do
        local tokensToDelete = playerTokens[playerColor]

        for _,tokenGUID in ipairs(tokensToDelete) do
            local token = getObjectFromGUID(tokenGUID)

            destroyObject(token)
        end
    end
end

-- Returns a random number between -1 and 1
function random()
    return (math.random() * 2) - 1
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    local playerSequence = {"Red", "Green", "Blue", "Yellow"}

    -- First, make sure that everyone has chosen a valid color
    for _,v in ipairs(Player.getPlayers()) do
        if findIndex(playerSequence, v.color) == 0 then
            broadcastToAll("Some players need to choose valid colors", {r=1, g=0, b=0})
            return
        end
    end

    -- Generate a list of seated players sorted by the order of
    -- colors on the table itself: Red, Green, Blue, Yellow
    local seatedPlayers = getSeatedPlayers()
    if #seatedPlayers < 2 then
        broadcastToAll("Not enough seated players", {r=1, g=0, b=0})
        return
    end

    -- A list of which players are seated, from left to right
    -- This is an array of player colors
    local seatedOrder = {}
    for _,v in ipairs(playerSequence) do
        if findIndex(seatedPlayers, v) > 0 then
            table.insert(seatedOrder, v)
        end
    end

    -- Choose one to be first
    local first = math.random(#seatedOrder)

    -- Create a table of the player order.  This is an array of player colors
    -- This is basically seatedOrder rotated so that the first player is
    -- the first element in the array.
    local playerOrder = {}
    for i = 1,#seatedOrder do
        table.insert(playerOrder, seatedOrder[first])
        first = first + 1
        if first > #seatedOrder then
            first = 1
        end
    end

    -- The locations where the player order tokens go
    local playerOrderTokenZones = {
        Red = getObjectFromGUID("dc5713"),
        Green = getObjectFromGUID("e696de"),
        Blue = getObjectFromGUID("aacb34"),
        Yellow = getObjectFromGUID("25d4d6"),
    }

    local playerMoneyZones = {
        Red = getObjectFromGUID("0c864b"),
        Green = getObjectFromGUID("f30c9d"),
        Blue = getObjectFromGUID("09fffe"),
        Yellow = getObjectFromGUID("67f67f"),
    }

    local moneyBags = {
        [1] = getObjectFromGUID("871136"),
        [5] = getObjectFromGUID("3fbf02"),
        [10] = getObjectFromGUID("2a92a3"),
    }

    -- Now deal out the player order tokens and money
    for k,playerColor in pairs(playerOrder) do
        local targetZone = playerOrderTokenZones[playerColor]
        local params = {
            smooth = false,
            position = targetZone.getPosition(),
            guid = orderTokenGUIDs[k],
        }
        orderBag.takeObject(params)

        -- Each player starts with $6
        local targetZone = playerMoneyZones[playerColor]
        local zoneSize = targetZone.getScale()
        local params = {
            smooth = false,
        }
        for i = 1,6 do
            -- Distribute the coins, but make sure they're distributed
            -- randomly so that they don't create a sticky stack
            local pos = targetZone.getPosition()
            pos.x = pos.x + random() * zoneSize.x / 4
            pos.z = pos.z + random() * zoneSize.z / 4
            pos.y = pos.y + i
            params.position = pos
            moneyBags[1].takeObject(params)
        end
    end

    createStructureTileClones()

    -- Remove all the objects associated with player colors not at the table
    local missingPlayers = {}
    for _,v in ipairs(Player.getAvailableColors()) do
        local index = findIndex(seatedPlayers, v)
        if index == 0 then
            table.insert(missingPlayers, v)
        end
    end

    -- if we're playing with more than 2 players, delete the neutral player too
    if #seatedOrder > 2 then
        table.insert(missingPlayers, "Neutral")
    end

    deleteOtherPlayers(missingPlayers)

    -- Two-player rules require additional setup
    if #seatedOrder == 2 then
        -- We need to wait one frame to give the structure tile scripting zones
        -- time to notice all these cloned tiles inside them.
        Wait.frames(function() twoPlayers(seatedOrder) end, 1)
    end
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
owner = nil -- who owns this tile
stack_zone = nil -- the scripting zone that covers the tile stack
colormap = {Red = {0.75, 0, 0}, Green = {0.25, 0.63, 0.2}, Blue = {0.1, 0.35, 0.65}, Yellow = {1, 1, 0}}

function onLoad(save_state)
    if save_state ~= "" then
        owner = save_state
    end

    stack_zone = getObjectFromGUID('c1a842')
end

-- if a player picks up a piece and it's not already owned, then assign it
function onPickUp(player)
    color = colormap[player]

    if not color then
        print("Unknown color ", player)
        return
    end

    if owner == nil then
        owner = player
        self.setColorTint(color)
    end
end

-- if the player drops the piece back on its stack, then reset it
function onDrop(player)
    local inStack = false

    for _,v in ipairs(stack_zone.getObjects()) do
        if v == self then
            owner = nil
            self.setColorTint({0.7, 0.7, 0.7}) -- grey
            break
        end
    end
end

function onSave()
    return owner or ""
end

ObjectStates.Name: BlockSquare
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad(save_state)
    self.interactable = false

    local params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 180, 0},
        label          = "District\nBonus",
        width          = 1800,
        height         = 1200,
        font_size      = 500,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Click this button to calculate the current district bonus scores."
    }
    self.createButton(params)
end

-- returns the index in table where 'value' exist, or 0
function findIndex(table, value)
    for k,v in pairs(table) do
        if v == value then
            return k
        end
    end

    return 0
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    local gameBoard = getObjectFromGUID("e2f237")
    local buttonSet = gameBoard.getVar("buttons_set")

    -- Build an array of districts from the buttonSet data.
    -- This matches the order of zones in Global.boardZones,
    -- so include that as well while we're at it
    local districts = {}
    local boardZones = Global.getVar("boardZones")

    for k,v in pairs(buttonSet) do
        local d = v.column * 5 + v.row + 1

        if districts[d] == nil then
            districts[d] = { Red = 0, Green = 0, Blue = 0, Yellow = 0, City = 0, Neutral = 0,
                zone = boardZones[d], count = 0, first = {}, second = {} }
            -- the central district has a city well marker that is not recorded,
            -- so mark it here.
            if d == 13 then
                districts[d].City = 1
            end
        end
        if v.cube_color then
            districts[d][v.cube_color] = districts[d][v.cube_color] + 1
        end
    end

    -- Who has the most and second-most number of cubes?
    for _,district in ipairs(districts) do
        local most = { 0, 0 }

        for _,c in ipairs({"Red", "Green", "Blue", "Yellow", "City", "Neutral"}) do
            if district[c] > most[1] then
                most[2] = most[1]
                most[1] = district[c]
            elseif district[c] > most[2] then
                most[2] = district[c]
            end
        end

        -- Now make a list of each color that is in first and second place
        -- Not sure if this is the best algorithm, but it appears to work
        for _,c in ipairs({"Red", "Green", "Blue", "Yellow", "City", "Neutral"}) do
            if most[1] > 0 and district[c] == most[1] then
                table.insert(district["first"], c)
            elseif most[2] > 0 and district[c] == most[2] then
                table.insert(district["second"], c)
            end
        end
    end

    -- Now figure out how many tiles are in each zone
    for k,district in pairs(districts) do
        local tiles = district["zone"].getObjects()

        -- Now we need to figure out how big each tile is. I really wish
        -- TTS let us store metadata with each object.  For now, just use
        -- the structure name.  Note that the City Well has a unique name,
        -- and it should be ignored anyway, so this works out.
        local count = 0
        local smallStructures = {"Well", "Garden", "Chapel", "Watchtower", "Merchant Stall", "Pageant Wagon" }
        local mediumStructures = {"Fountain", "Farm", "Church", "Garrison", "Marketplace", "Stage" }
        local largeStructures = {"Water Works", "Granary", "Cathedral", "Citadel", "Guild Hall", "Town Square" }

        for _,tile in ipairs(tiles) do
            local name = tile.getName()
            if findIndex(smallStructures, name) > 0 then
                count = count + 1
            elseif findIndex(mediumStructures, name) > 0 then
                count = count + 2
            elseif findIndex(largeStructures, name) > 0 then
                count = count + 4
            end
        end

        district["count"] = count
    end

    -- Now add up the points for each district
    local points = { Red = 0, Blue = 0, Green = 0, Yellow = 0, City = 0, Neutral = 0}
    for k,district in pairs(districts) do
        if #district["first"] > 0 then
            local firstScore = math.floor(district["count"] / #district["first"])

            for _,v in ipairs(district["first"]) do
                points[v] = points[v] + firstScore
            end

            -- Second place scoring is award only if one player gets second place
            local second = district["second"]
            if #second == 1 then
                points[second[1]] = points[second[1]] + math.floor(firstScore / 2)
            end
        end
    end

    local Red = getObjectFromGUID("70add7")
    local Green = getObjectFromGUID("f29f5a")
    local Blue = getObjectFromGUID("5e0202")
    local Yellow = getObjectFromGUID("467c8e")

    Red.editButton({index = 0, label=points["Red"]})
    Green.editButton({index = 0, label=points["Green"]})
    Blue.editButton({index = 0, label=points["Blue"]})
    Yellow.editButton({index = 0, label=points["Yellow"]})
end

function nop()
end

    }

-- Remind the player of the breaking ground bonus, if applicable
function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, obj)
    for k,v in pairs(boardZones) do
        if v == zone then
            if #zone.getObjects() == 1 then
                local playerColor = obj.getVar("owner")

                -- Ignore anything dropped that isn't a structure tile
                if not playerColor then
                    break
                end

                -- In single-player mode, only one color "exists" at a time,
                -- which means that if a player drops a tile that belongs to
                -- another player, then playerColor will technically be a
                -- color that doesn't exist, so we can't use it.
                if not Player[playerColor].seated then
                    break
                end

                printToColor("Don't forget the breaking ground bonus: one point " ..
                    "for each service provided in the new district at the end of your turn.",
                    playerColor, playerColor)
            end

            break
        end
    end
end
